<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; MARGIN-LEFT:2%">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<I>
	Senior Secured Credit
	Facilities And Other Senior Secured Debt&nbsp;(continued)
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PX;MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Borrowings under the senior secured credit facilities bear interest at a
	rate equal to, at our option, either (a)&nbsp;a base rate determined by reference to the higher of (1)&nbsp;the federal funds rate plus 0.50% or (2)&nbsp;the prime rate of Bank of America or (b)&nbsp;a LIBOR rate for the currency of such borrowing
	for the relevant interest period, plus, in each case, an applicable margin. The applicable margin for borrowings under the senior secured credit facilities may be reduced subject to attaining certain leverage ratios.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The senior secured credit facilities contain a number of covenants that restrict, subject to certain exceptions, our (and
	some or all of our subsidiaries&#146;) ability to incur additional indebtedness, repay subordinated indebtedness, create liens on assets, sell assets, make investments, loans or advances, engage in certain transactions with affiliates, pay dividends
	and distributions, and enter into sale and leaseback transactions. In addition, we are required to satisfy and maintain a maximum total leverage ratio covenant under the cash flow credit facility and, in certain situations under the ABL credit
	facility, a minimum interest coverage ratio covenant.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Senior secured notes consists of
	(i)&nbsp;$3.000&nbsp;billion aggregate principal amount of 6.50% first lien notes due 2020; (ii)&nbsp;$1.350&nbsp;billion aggregate principal amount of 5.875% first lien notes due 2022; (iii)&nbsp;$1.250&nbsp;billion aggregate principal amount of
	4.75% first lien notes due 2023; (iv)&nbsp;$1.500&nbsp;billion aggregate principal amount of 3.75% first lien notes due 2019; (v)&nbsp;$2.000&nbsp;billion aggregate principal amount of 5.00% first lien notes due 2024; (vi)&nbsp;$600&nbsp;million
	aggregate principal amount of 4.25% first lien notes due 2019; (vii)&nbsp;$1.400&nbsp;billion aggregate principal amount of 5.25% first lien notes due 2025; (viii)&nbsp;$1.500&nbsp;billion aggregate principal amount of 5.25% first lien notes due
	2026; and (ix)&nbsp;$1.200&nbsp;billion aggregate principal amount of 4.50% first lien notes due 2027. Capital leases and other secured debt totaled $593&nbsp;million at December&nbsp;31, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	We use interest rate swap agreements to manage the variable rate exposure of our debt portfolio. At December&nbsp;31,
	2016, we had entered into effective interest rate swap agreements, in a total notional amount of $3.000&nbsp;billion, in order to hedge a portion of our exposure to variable rate interest payments associated with the senior secured credit
	facilities. The effect of the interest rate swaps is reflected in the effective interest rates for the senior secured credit facilities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; MARGIN-LEFT:2%">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<I>
	Senior Unsecured Notes
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Senior unsecured notes consist of
	(i)&nbsp;$8.391&nbsp;billion aggregate principal amount of senior notes with maturities ranging from 2018 to 2033; (ii)&nbsp;an aggregate principal amount of $125&nbsp;million medium-term notes maturing 2025; (iii)&nbsp;an aggregate principal amount
	of $736&nbsp;million debentures with maturities ranging from 2023 to 2095; and (iv)&nbsp;an aggregate principal amount of $1.000&nbsp;billion senior notes due 2021.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; MARGIN-LEFT:2%">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<I>
	General Debt Information
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The senior secured credit
	facilities and senior secured notes are fully and unconditionally guaranteed by substantially all existing and future, direct and indirect, 100% owned material domestic subsidiaries that are &#147;Unrestricted Subsidiaries&#148; under our Indenture
	(the &#147;1993 Indenture&#148;) dated December&nbsp;16, 1993 (except for certain special purpose subsidiaries that only guarantee and pledge their assets under our ABL credit facility).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	All obligations under the ABL credit facility, and the guarantees of those obligations, are secured, subject to permitted
	liens and other exceptions, by a first-priority lien on substantially all of the receivables of the borrowers and each guarantor under such ABL credit facility (the &#147;Receivables Collateral&#148;).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">

	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Our senior secured notes and the related guarantees are secured by first-priority liens, subject to permitted liens, on
	our and our subsidiary guarantors&#146; assets, subject to certain exceptions, that secure our cash flow credit facility on a first-priority basis and are secured by second-priority liens, subject to permitted liens, on our and our subsidiary
	guarantors&#146; assets that secure our ABL credit facility on a first-priority basis and our other cash flow credit facility on a second-priority basis.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Maturities of long-term debt in years 2018 through 2021, excluding amounts under the ABL credit facility, are $691&nbsp;million, $2.264&nbsp;billion, $4.163&nbsp;billion and $1.065&nbsp;billion,
	respectively.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	NOTE 10 &#151; CONTINGENCIES AND LEGAL CLAIM COSTS
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	We operate in a highly regulated and litigious industry. As a result, various lawsuits, claims and legal and regulatory
	proceedings have been and can be expected to be instituted or asserted against us. We are also subject to claims and suits arising in the ordinary course of business, including claims for personal injuries or wrongful restriction of, or interference
	with, physicians&#146; staff privileges. In certain of these actions the claimants may seek punitive damages against us which may not be covered by insurance. We are also subject to claims by various taxing authorities for additional taxes and
	related interest and penalties. The resolution of any such lawsuits, claims or legal and regulatory proceedings could have a material, adverse effect on our results of operations, financial position or liquidity.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; MARGIN-LEFT:2%">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<I>
	Government Investigations, Claims and Litigation
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Health care companies are subject to numerous investigations by various governmental agencies. Under the federal False
	Claims Act (&#147;FCA&#148;), private parties have the right to bring
<I>
	qui tam
</I>
	, or &#147;whistleblower,&#148; suits against companies that submit false claims for payments to, or improperly retain overpayments from, the government. Some states
	have adopted similar state whistleblower and false claims provisions. Certain of our individual facilities have received, and from time to time, other facilities may receive, government inquiries from, and may be subject to investigation by, federal
	and state agencies. Depending on whether the underlying conduct in these or future inquiries or investigations could be considered systemic, their resolution could have a material, adverse effect on our results of operations, financial position or
	liquidity.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; MARGIN-LEFT:2%">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<I>
	Health Midwest Litigation
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	In October 2009, the Health Care Foundation of Greater Kansas City, a nonprofit health foundation, filed suit against HCA
	Inc. in the Circuit Court of Jackson County, Missouri and alleged that HCA did not fund the level of
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	F-28
</FONT>
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage121"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D299981D10K_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	HCA HOLDINGS, INC.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS&nbsp;(Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	NOTE 10 &#151; CONTINGENCIES AND LEGAL CLAIM COSTS&nbsp;(continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; MARGIN-LEFT:2%">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<I>
	Health Midwest Litigation&nbsp;(continued)
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PX;MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	capital expenditures and uncompensated care agreed to in connection with HCA&#146;s purchase of hospitals from Health Midwest in 2003. The central issue in the case was whether HCA&#146;s
	construction of new hospitals counted towards its $450&nbsp;million five-year capital commitment. In addition, the plaintiff alleged that HCA did not make its required capital expenditures in a timely fashion. On January&nbsp;24, 2013, the court
	ruled in favor of the plaintiff and awarded at least $162&nbsp;million. The court also ordered a court-supervised accounting of HCA&#146;s capital expenditures, as well as of expenditures on charity and uncompensated care during the ten years
	following the purchase. The court also indicated it would award plaintiff attorneys fees, which the parties stipulated were approximately $12&nbsp;million for the trial phase. HCA recorded $175&nbsp;million of legal claim costs in the fourth quarter
	of 2012 related to this ruling, and consistent with the judge&#146;s order, accrued interest on that sum at 9%&nbsp;per annum. On April&nbsp;25, 2014, the parties stipulated to an additional $78&nbsp;million shortfall relating to the capital
	expenditures issue. HCA recorded $78&nbsp;million of legal claims costs in the first quarter of 2014 as a result of the stipulation, and accrued interest on that amount at 9%&nbsp;per annum. Pursuant to the terms of the stipulation, the parties
	preserved their respective rights to contest the judge&#146;s underlying ruling, whether through motions in the trial court or on appeal. On February&nbsp;9, 2015, the parties reached an agreement to settle the part of their dispute relating to
	charity and uncompensated care for $15&nbsp;million. The foundation is required to use that amount, net of attorneys&#146; fees, for charitable activities in the Kansas City area. The parties also agreed on an additional amount for attorneys&#146;
	fees for the plaintiff for the accounting phase of the case. The parties filed post-trial motions, on which the court ruled on October&nbsp;21, 2015. The court denied defendants&#146; motion to have the court change its rulings on liability and
	damages related to the capital expenditures issue. The court granted the plaintiff&#146;s motion for an award of additional
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	pre-judgment
</FONT>
	interest, but did not specify whether the interest awarded was simple
	interest or would be compounded. The court subsequently concluded that interest was to be compounded, and on December&nbsp;9, 2015, the court entered judgment in the case in the total sum of $434&nbsp;million, with interest continuing to accrue at
	9%&nbsp;per annum, compounded annually, from and after November&nbsp;19, 2015, until the matter is resolved. On January 15, 2016, HCA filed a Notice of Appeal in the Missouri Court of Appeals for the Western District, and oral arguments were
	presented during December 2016. On January 17, 2017, the Court of Appeals issued an opinion that partly affirmed and partly overruled the trial court. The Court of Appeals ruled that the construction of new hospitals did qualify as capital
	expenditures, and that HCA had met its overall $450 million five-year capital commitment. The Court of Appeals ruled, however, that certain interim milestones were not properly met, and consequently found HCA liable to the foundation for a shortfall
	amount plus attorneys&#146; fees. The Court of Appeals reversed the trial court on the issues of pre-judgement interest and compounding of interest. It entered a modified judgement in the amount of $188 million, plus post-judgement interest accruing
	at 9% per annum, simple interest, beginning in December 2015. The parties subsequently reached a settlement whereby each side gave up their rights to seek further review in the Missouri Supreme Court in return for payment by HCA of $188 million (no
	interest was paid in the settlement), which payment was made on February 1, 2017. The settlement agreement enabled HCA to reduce the accrual for this claim by $290 million and resulted in the recognition of net legal claim benefits of $246 million
	for the year ended December 31, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	F-29

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	NOTE 12 &#151; CAPITAL STOCK
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The amended and restated certificate of incorporation authorizes the Company to issue up to 1,800,000,000 shares of common
	stock, and our amended and restated
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	by-laws
</FONT>
	set the number of directors constituting the board of directors of the Company at not less than three members, the exact number to be determined from time to time by
	resolution adopted by the affirmative vote of a majority of the total number of directors then in office.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; MARGIN-LEFT:2%">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<I>
	Share Repurchase
	Transactions
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	During November 2016, our board of directors authorized a share repurchase program for up to
	$2&nbsp;billion of our outstanding common stock. During May 2016, the Company repurchased 9.361&nbsp;million shares of its common stock beneficially owned by affiliates of Kohlberg Kravis Roberts&nbsp;&amp; Co. at a purchase price of $80.12 per
	share, the closing price of the Company&#146;s common stock on the New York Stock Exchange on May&nbsp;10, 2016, less a discount of 1%. During 2016, we also repurchased 26.964&nbsp;million shares of our common stock at an average price of $74.20 per
	share through market purchases, resulting in total repurchases of 36.325&nbsp;million shares of our common stock at an average price of $75.72 per share for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2016 pursuant to the $3&nbsp;billion October 2015 (which
	was completed during the fourth quarter of 2016) and the $2&nbsp;billion November 2016 share repurchase programs. At December&nbsp;31, 2016, we had $1.853&nbsp;billion of repurchase authorization available under the November 2016 authorization.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	During October 2015,&nbsp;May 2015 and February 2015, our board of directors authorized share repurchase
	programs for up to $3&nbsp;billion, $1&nbsp;billion and $1&nbsp;billion, respectively, of our outstanding common stock. During April 2015, the Company entered into an agreement to repurchase 3.806&nbsp;million shares of its common stock beneficially
	owned by affiliates of Bain Capital Investors, LLC (the &#147;Bain Entities&#148;) and certain charitable organizations that received shares of common stock as charitable contributions from certain partners and other employees of the Bain Entities
	at a purchase price of $77.26 per share, the closing price of the Company&#146;s common stock on the New York Stock Exchange on April&nbsp;17, 2015, less a discount of 1% (the &#147;Share Repurchase&#148;). The Share Repurchase was made pursuant to
	the February 2015 authorization. During 2015, we also repurchased 28.185&nbsp;million shares of our common stock at an average price of $74.62 per share through market purchases, resulting in total repurchases pursuant to the October 2015,&nbsp;May
	2015 and February 2015
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	F-30
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	HCA HOLDINGS, INC.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS&nbsp;(Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	NOTE 12 &#151; CAPITAL STOCK&nbsp;(continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; MARGIN-LEFT:2%">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<I>
	Share Repurchase
	Transactions&nbsp;(continued)
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PX;MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	authorizations of 31.991&nbsp;million shares of our common stock at an average price of $74.93 per share. At December&nbsp;31, 2015, we had no repurchase authorization remaining under the
	$1.0&nbsp;billion May 2015 and $1.0&nbsp;billion February 2015 authorizations and $2.603&nbsp;billion of repurchase authorization available under the $3.0&nbsp;billion October 2015 authorization.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	During December 2014, the Company entered into an agreement to repurchase 7.613&nbsp;million shares of its common stock
	beneficially owned by affiliates of Bain Capital Investors, LLC at a purchase price of $73.26 per share, the closing price of the Company&#146;s common stock on the New York Stock Exchange on December&nbsp;5, 2014, less a discount of 1%. The
	repurchase was made pursuant to the Company&#146;s $1&nbsp;billion repurchase program adopted by the Company&#146;s board of directors in October 2014 which was completed during the fourth quarter of 2014 through market purchases of an additional
	6.416&nbsp;million shares of our common stock at an average purchase price of $68.96 per share (14.029&nbsp;million total shares repurchased at an average purchase price of $71.29 per share).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	During May 2014, certain of the Company&#146;s stockholders, consisting principally of affiliates of, or funds sponsored
	by, Bain Capital Partners, LLC and Kohlberg Kravis Roberts&nbsp;&amp; Co. (the &#147;Selling Stockholders&#148;), sold in an underwritten secondary offering, 15&nbsp;million shares from their holdings of the Company&#146;s common stock. The Selling
	Shareholders received all the proceeds from this offering. Concurrent with the closing of the secondary offering, we repurchased approximately $750&nbsp;million of additional shares (14.555&nbsp;million shares) of our common stock from the Selling
	Stockholders at the net offering price ($51.53 per share).
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	NOTE 13 &#151; EMPLOYEE BENEFIT PLANS
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	We maintain defined contribution benefit plans that are available to employees who meet certain minimum requirements.
	Certain of the plans require that we match specified percentages of participant contributions up to certain maximum levels (generally, 100% of the first 3% to 9%, depending upon years of vesting service, of compensation deferred by participants).
	The cost of these plans totaled $444&nbsp;million for 2016, $432&nbsp;million for 2015 and $404&nbsp;million for 2014. Our contributions are funded periodically during each year.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	We maintain the noncontributory, nonqualified Restoration Plan to provide certain retirement benefits for eligible
	employees. Eligibility for the Restoration Plan is based upon earning eligible compensation in excess of the Social Security Wage Base and attaining 1,000 or more hours of service during the plan year. Company credits to participants&#146; account
	balances (the Restoration Plan is not funded) depend upon participants&#146; compensation, years of vesting service and certain IRS limitations related to the HCA 401(k) plan. Benefits expense under this plan was $20&nbsp;million for 2016,
	$20&nbsp;million for 2015 and $31&nbsp;million for 2014. Accrued benefits liabilities under this plan totaled $175&nbsp;million at December&nbsp;31, 2016 and $164&nbsp;million at December&nbsp;31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	We maintain a Supplemental Executive Retirement Plan (&#147;SERP&#148;) for certain executives (the SERP is not funded).
	The plan is designed to ensure that upon retirement the participant receives the value of a prescribed life annuity from the combination of the SERP and our other benefit plans. Benefits expense under the plan was $22&nbsp;million for 2016,
	$33&nbsp;million for 2015 and $31&nbsp;million for 2014. Accrued benefits liabilities under this plan totaled $222&nbsp;million at December&nbsp;31, 2016 and $207&nbsp;million at December&nbsp;31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	We maintain defined benefit pension plans which resulted from certain hospital acquisitions in prior years. Benefits
	expense under these plans was $21&nbsp;million for 2016, $25&nbsp;million for 2015, and $13&nbsp;million for 2014. Accrued benefits liabilities under these plans totaled $111&nbsp;million at December&nbsp;31, 2016 and $131&nbsp;million at
	December&nbsp;31, 2015.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT SIZE="1">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	F-31

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	NOTE 14 &#151; SEGMENT AND GEOGRAPHIC INFORMATION
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	We operate in one line of business, which is operating hospitals and related health care entities. We operate in two
	geographically organized groups: the National and American Groups. At December&nbsp;31, 2016, the National Group included 84 hospitals located in Alaska, California, Florida, southern Georgia, Idaho, Indiana, northern Kentucky, Nevada, New
	Hampshire, South Carolina, Utah and Virginia, and the American Group included 80 hospitals located in Colorado, northern Georgia, Kansas, southern Kentucky, Louisiana, Mississippi, Missouri, Oklahoma, Tennessee and Texas. We also operate six
	hospitals in England, and these facilities are included in the Corporate and other group.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Adjusted segment
	EBITDA is defined as income before depreciation and amortization, interest expense, losses (gains) on sales of facilities, losses on retirement of debt, legal claim costs (benefits), income taxes and net income attributable to noncontrolling
	interests. We use adjusted segment EBITDA as an analytical indicator for purposes of allocating resources to geographic areas and assessing their performance. Adjusted segment EBITDA is commonly used as an analytical indicator within the health care
	industry, and also serves as a measure of leverage capacity and debt service ability. Adjusted segment EBITDA should not be considered as a measure of financial performance under generally accepted accounting principles, and the items excluded from
	adjusted segment EBITDA are significant components in understanding and assessing financial performance. Because adjusted segment EBITDA is not a measurement determined in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles and is thus
	susceptible to varying calculations, adjusted segment EBITDA, as presented, may not be comparable to other similarly titled measures of other companies. The geographic distributions of our revenues, equity in earnings of affiliates, adjusted segment
	EBITDA, depreciation and amortization, assets and goodwill and other intangible assets are summarized in the following table (dollars in millions):
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PX;MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
	&nbsp;
</P>

	HCA Inc. is a 100% owned direct subsidiary of HCA
	Holdings, Inc. On November&nbsp;23, 2010, HCA Holdings, Inc. issued $1.525&nbsp;billion aggregate principal amount of
	7

<SUP STYLE="VERTICAL-ALIGN:BASELINE; POSITION:RELATIVE; BOTTOM:.8EX">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	% senior unsecured notes due 2021, which were redeemed in full during May 2015. On December&nbsp;6, 2012, HCA Holdings,
	Inc. issued $1.000&nbsp;billion aggregate principal amount of 6.25% senior unsecured notes due 2021. These notes are senior unsecured obligations and are not guaranteed by any of our subsidiaries.
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	The senior secured credit facilities and senior secured notes described in Note 9 are jointly and severally, and fully
	and unconditionally guaranteed by substantially all existing and future, direct and indirect, 100% owned material domestic subsidiaries that are &#147;Unrestricted Subsidiaries&#148; under our Indenture dated December&nbsp;16, 1993 (except for
	certain special purpose subsidiaries that only guarantee and pledge their assets under our ABL credit facility).
</FONT>
</P>

<H5 ALIGN="LEFT">
<A HREF="#D299981D10K_HTM_TOC">
	Table of Contents
</A>
</H5>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	HCA HOLDINGS, INC.
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS&nbsp;(Continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; MARGIN-LEFT:12%; TEXT-INDENT:-12%">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	NOTE 17 &#151; SUPPLEMENTAL CONDENSED CONSOLIDATING FINANCIAL INFORMATION AND OTHER COLLATERAL-RELATED
	INFORMATION&nbsp;(continued)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:6PX;MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Healthtrust, Inc. &#151; The Hospital Company (&#147;Healthtrust&#148;)
	is the first-tier subsidiary of HCA Inc. The common stock of Healthtrust has been pledged as collateral for the senior secured credit facilities and senior secured notes described in Note 9. Rule
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	3-16
</FONT>
	of
	Regulation
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	S-X
</FONT>
	under the Securities Act requires the filing of separate financial statements for any affiliate of the registrant whose securities constitute a substantial portion of the collateral for any
	class of securities registered or being registered. We believe the separate financial statements requirement applies to Healthtrust due to the pledge of its common stock as collateral for the senior secured notes. Due to the corporate structure
	relationship of HCA and Healthtrust, HCA&#146;s operating subsidiaries are also the operating subsidiaries of Healthtrust. The corporate structure relationship, combined with the application of push-down accounting in Healthtrust&#146;s consolidated
	financial statements related to HCA&#146;s debt and financial instruments, results in the consolidated financial statements of Healthtrust being substantially identical to the consolidated financial statements of HCA. The consolidated financial
	statements of HCA and Healthtrust present the identical amounts for revenues, expenses, net income, assets, liabilities, total stockholders&#146; deficit, net cash provided by operating activities, net cash used in investing activities and net cash
	used in financing activities. Certain individual line items in the HCA consolidated statements of stockholders&#146; deficit are combined into one line item in the Healthtrust consolidated statements of stockholder&#146;s deficit.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	Reconciliations of the HCA Holdings, Inc. Consolidated Statements of Stockholders&#146; Deficit presentation to the
	Healthtrust, Inc. &#151; The Hospital Company Consolidated Statements of Stockholder&#146;s Deficit presentation for the years ended December&nbsp;31, 2016, 2015 and 2014 are as follows (dollars in millions):
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PX;MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="FONT-SIZE:12PX;MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX">
	&nbsp;
</P>

<EFX_EXHIBIT_10>
<A NAME="FIS_EXHIBIT_10"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="RIGHT">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	Exhibit 10.16(l)
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	FOURTH AMENDMENT TO
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	THIS AMENDMENT TO EMPLOYMENT
	AGREEMENT
</B>
	(the &#147;Amendment&#148;) is made by and between
<B>
	Samuel N. Hazen
</B>
	(the &#147;Executive&#148;) and
<B>
	HCA Holdings, Inc.
</B>
	, a Delaware corporation (the &#147;Company&#148;), effective as of November&nbsp;14, 2016.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	WITNESSETH:
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	WHEREAS,
</B>
	HCA Inc. previously entered into an Employment Agreement (the &#147;Employment Agreement&#148;) with the Executive dated November&nbsp;16, 2006;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	WHEREAS,
</B>
	on November&nbsp;22, 2010, the Company completed a corporate reorganization pursuant to which the Company
	became the direct parent company of, and successor issuer to, HCA Inc. (the &#147;Corporate Reorganization&#148;);
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	WHEREAS,
</B>
	the Company assumed the Employment Agreement in connection with the Corporate Reorganization;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	WHEREAS,
</B>
	the Employment Agreement was previously amended effective February&nbsp;9, 2011,&nbsp;January&nbsp;29, 2015 and January&nbsp;27, 2016; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	WHEREAS,
</B>
	the Company and the Executive desire to further amend the Employment Agreement as provided herein.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	NOW, THEREFORE,
</B>
	for the reasons set forth above, and other valid consideration, the receipt of which
	is hereby acknowledged, the Company and the Executive hereby amend the Employment Agreement as follows:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	1.
<U>
	Amendments
</U>
	. Section&nbsp;2(a) of the Employment Agreement is deleted in its entirety and replaced with the following:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	&#147;a. During the Employment Term, Executive shall serve as the President and Chief Operating Officer of the Company. In such position, Executive shall have such duties, authority and responsibility as
	shall be determined from time to time by the Chief Executive Officer which duties, authority and responsibility are consistent with those attendant to such position with the Company with respect to the business of the Company. Executive shall, if
	requested, also serve as a member of the Board of Directors of any affiliate of the Company, without additional compensation.&#148;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	2.
<U>
	Certain Definitions
</U>
	. Capitalized terms used in this Amendment not otherwise defined herein shall have the same meaning as set forth in the Employment Agreement.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	3.
<U>
	Effect of Amendment
</U>
	. Except as modified hereby, the Employment Agreement shall remain unaffected and in full
	force and effect.
</FONT>
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage139"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX; TEXT-INDENT:4%" ALIGN="JUSTIFY">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
	4.
<U>
	Counterparts
</U>
	. This Amendment may be executed in counterparts, each
	of which shall be an original but all of which shall constitute but one document.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">
<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<I>
	[Signature page follows]
</I>
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PX;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PX" ALIGN="CENTER">

<FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" SIZE="2">
<B>
	IN WITNESS WHEREOF,
</B>
	the undersigned have executed this Agreement,
	intending to be legally bound, as of the date first stated above.

<B>
	Form of HCA Holdings, Inc.
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<B>
	Stock Appreciation Rights Agreement
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	This STOCK APPRECIATION RIGHTS AGREEMENT (the &#147;
<U>
	Agreement
</U>
	&#148;), dated as of
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (the &#147;
<U>
	Grant Date
</U>
	&#148;) is made by and between HCA Holdings, Inc., a Delaware corporation (together with its
	Subsidiaries and other Service Recipients, hereinafter referred to as the &#147;
<U>
	Company
</U>
	&#148;), and the individual whose name is set forth below, who is an employee of the Company and hereinafter referred to as the &#147;
<U>
	Grantee
</U>
	&#148;.
	Any capitalized terms herein not otherwise defined in Article I shall have the meaning set forth in the 2006 Stock Incentive Plan for Key Employees of HCA Holdings, Inc. and its Affiliates, as amended and restated (the &#147;
<U>
	Plan
</U>
	&#148;).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	WHEREAS, the Company wishes to carry out the Plan, the terms of which are hereby incorporated by reference and made a part of this Agreement;
	and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	WHEREAS, the Compensation Committee of the Board of Directors of the Company, including any subcommittee formed pursuant to Section
	3(a) of the Plan, (or, if no such committee is appointed, the Board of Directors of the Company) (the &#147;
<U>
	Committee
</U>
	&#148;) has determined that it would be to the advantage and best interest of the Company and its shareholders to grant an
	award of Stock Appreciation Rights (&#147;
<U>
	SARs
</U>
	&#148;) as provided for herein to the Grantee as an incentive for increased efforts during his or her term of office, employment or service with the Company, and has advised the Company thereof
	and instructed the undersigned officers to issue said SARs;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants herein contained and
	other good and valuable consideration, receipt of which is hereby acknowledged, the parties hereto do hereby agree as follows:
</P>

	Grant Date of Award (&#147;Grant Date&#148;):

<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
</EFX_UNIDENTIFIED_TABLE>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	ARTICLE I
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<U>
	DEFINITIONS
</U>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Whenever the following terms are used in this Agreement, they shall have the meaning specified below unless the context clearly indicates to
	the contrary.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
<U>
	Section&nbsp;1.1.
</U>
	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Cause
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#147;Cause&#148; shall mean &#147;Cause&#148; as such term may be defined in any employment agreement or
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	change-in-control
</FONT>
</FONT>
	agreement in effect at the time of termination of employment between the Grantee and the Company or, if there is no such employment or
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	change-in-control
</FONT>
</FONT>
	agreement, &#147;Cause&#148; shall mean (i)&nbsp;willful and continued failure by Grantee (other than by reason of a Permanent Disability) to perform his or her material duties with respect
	to the Company which continues beyond ten (10)&nbsp;business days after a written demand for substantial performance is delivered to Grantee by the Company (the &#147;
<U>
	Cure Period
</U>
	&#148;); (ii) willful or intentional engaging by Grantee in
	material misconduct that causes material and demonstrable injury, monetarily or otherwise, to the Company or its Affiliates; (iii)&nbsp;conviction of, or a plea of nolo contendere to, a crime constituting (x)&nbsp;a felony under the laws of the
	United States or any state thereof or (y)&nbsp;a misdemeanor for which a sentence of more than six months&#146; imprisonment is imposed; or (iv)&nbsp;Grantee&#146;s engaging in any action in breach of restrictive covenants made by Grantee under any
	agreement containing restrictive covenants (e.g., covenants not to disclose confidential information, to compete with the business of the Company or to solicit the employees thereof to terminate their employment) or any employment or
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	change-in-control
</FONT>
</FONT>
	agreement between the Grantee and the Company, which continues beyond the Cure Period (to the extent that, in the Board&#146;s reasonable judgment, such
	breach can be cured).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;1.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Good
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Reason
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#147;Good Reason&#148; shall mean &#147;Good Reason&#148; as such term may be defined in any employment agreement or
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	change-in-control
</FONT>
</FONT>
	agreement in effect at the time of termination of employment between the Grantee and the Company, or, if there is no such employment or
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	change-in-control
</FONT>
</FONT>
	agreement, &#147;Good Reason&#148; shall mean (i)&nbsp;(A) a reduction in Grantee&#146;s base salary (other than a general reduction in base salary that
	affects all similarly situated employees (defined as all employees within the same Company pay grade as that of Grantee) in substantially the same proportions that the Board implements in good faith after consultation with the Chief Executive
	Officer and Chief Operating Officer of the Company, if any); (B) a reduction in Grantee&#146;s annual incentive compensation opportunity; or (C)&nbsp;the reduction of benefits payable to Grantee under the Company&#146;s Supplemental Executive
	Retirement Plan (if Grantee is a participant in such plan), in each case other than any isolated, insubstantial and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	2
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage143"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	inadvertent failure by the Company that is not in bad faith and is cured within ten (10)&nbsp;business days after Grantee gives the Company written notice of such event;
<U>
	provided
</U>
	that the
	events described in (i)(A) or (i)(B) above will not be deemed to give rise to Good Reason if employment is terminated, but Grantee declines an offer of employment involving a loss of compensation of less than 15% from a purchaser, transferee,
	outsourced vendor, new operating entity or affiliated employer; (ii)&nbsp;a substantial diminution in Grantee&#146;s title, duties and responsibilities, other than any isolated, insubstantial and inadvertent failure by the Company that is not in bad
	faith and is cured within ten (10)&nbsp;business days after Grantee gives the Company written notice of such event; or (iii)&nbsp;a transfer of Grantee&#146;s primary workplace to a location that is more than twenty (20)&nbsp;miles from his or her
	workplace as of the date of this Agreement;
<U>
	provided
</U>
	that Good Reason shall not be deemed to occur merely because Grantee&#146;s willful decision to change position or status within the Company causes one or more of the occurrences described
	in (i), (ii), or (iii)&nbsp;to come about.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;1.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Permanent
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Disability
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#147;Permanent Disability&#148; shall mean &#147;Disability&#148; as such term is defined in any employment agreement between Grantee and the
	Company, or, if there is no such employment agreement, &#147;Disability&#148; as defined in the long-term disability plan of the Company.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;1.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Retirement
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#147;Retirement&#148; shall mean Grantee&#146;s resignation (other than for Good Reason) from service with the Company (i)&nbsp;after
	attaining 65 years of age or (ii)&nbsp;after attaining 55 years of age and completing ten (10)&nbsp;years of service with the Company.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;1.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	SARs
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#147;SARs&#148; shall mean the aggregate of the SARs granted under Section&nbsp;2.1 of this Agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;1.6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Secretary
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	&#147;Secretary&#148; shall mean the Secretary of the Company.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	ARTICLE II
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<U>
	GRANT OF SARS
</U>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;2.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Grant
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	of
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	SARs
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	For good and valuable consideration, on and as of the date hereof the Company grants to the Grantee an award of SARs (the
	&#147;
<U>
	Award
</U>
	&#148;) on the terms
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	3
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage144"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	and conditions set forth in this Agreement. Each SAR represents the right to receive pursuant to this Agreement, upon exercise of the SAR, a payment from the Company in shares of Common Stock
	having a value equal to the excess of the Fair Market Value of one Share on the exercise date over the Base Price (as defined below).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;2.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Base
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Price
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Subject to Section&nbsp;2.4, the base price of each SAR granted pursuant to this Agreement (the &#147;
<U>
	Base Price
</U>
	&#148;) shall be as set
	forth on the first page of this Agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;2.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	No
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Guarantee
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	of
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Employment
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Nothing in this Agreement or in the Plan shall confer upon the Grantee any right to continue in the employ of
	the Company nor interfere with or restrict in any way the rights of the Company, which are hereby expressly reserved, to terminate the employment of the Grantee at any time for any reason whatsoever, with or without cause, subject to the applicable
	provisions of, if any, the Grantee&#146;s employment agreement with the Company or offer letter provided by the Company to the Grantee.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;2.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Adjustments
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	to
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	SARs
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	The SARs shall be subject to the adjustment provisions of Sections 8 and 9 of the Plan,
<U>
	provided
</U>
	,
<U>
	however
</U>
	, that in the event of
	the payment of an extraordinary dividend by the Company to its stockholders, then:
<U>
	first
</U>
	, the Base Price of each SAR shall be reduced by the amount of the dividend per share paid, but only to the extent the Committee determines it to be
	permitted under applicable tax laws and it will not have adverse tax consequences to the Grantee; and, if such reduction cannot be fully effected due to such tax laws,
<U>
	second
</U>
	, the Company shall pay to the Grantee a cash payment, on a per SAR
	basis, equal to the balance of the amount of the dividend not permitted to be applied to reduce the Base Price of the applicable SARs as follows: (a)&nbsp;for each Share with respect to which a vested SAR relates, promptly following the date of such
	dividend payment; and (b), for each Share with respect to which an unvested SAR relates, on the date on which such SAR becomes vested and exercisable with respect to such Share.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	ARTICLE III
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<U>
	PERIOD OF
	EXERCISABILITY
</U>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;3.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Commencement
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	of
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Exercisability
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;So long as the Grantee continues to be employed by the Company, this Award shall become vested and exercisable with
	respect to 25%
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	4
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage145"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	of the SARs on each of the first four anniversaries of the Grant Date (each such date, a &#147;
<U>
	Vesting Date
</U>
	&#148;). Except as provided in
<U>
	Section 3.1(b)
</U>
	, or as otherwise provided by
	the Committee, no part of this Award shall become vested as to any additional SARs as of any date following the termination of Grantee&#146;s employment with the Company for any reason and any SAR, which is (or determined to be) unvested as of the
	Grantee&#146;s termination of employment, shall immediately expire without payment therefor.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Notwithstanding
	the foregoing, upon the occurrence of a Change in Control (the definition of which is set forth on
<U>
	Schedule A
</U>
	attached hereto):
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:13%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(1)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event the entity surviving the Change in Control (the &#147;
<U>
	Successor
</U>
	&#148;) assumes the Award
	granted hereby, if the Grantee&#146;s employment with the Successor is terminated without Cause by the Successor, or terminates for Good Reason by the Grantee or on account of Grantee&#146;s death or Permanent Disability prior to an applicable
	Vesting Date, all unvested SARs not previously forfeited shall immediately vest and become exercisable as of the date of such termination of employment for the applicable period set forth in Section&nbsp;3.2.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:13%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(2)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event the Successor does not assume the Award granted hereby, all unvested SARs not previously forfeited
	shall vest immediately prior to the effective date of the Change in Control, and shall be cancelled in exchange for the payment described in Section 9(a)(ii)(A) of the Plan as of the effective date of the Change in Control.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;3.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Expiration
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	of
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	SARs
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	The Grantee may not exercise any SAR granted pursuant to this Award after the first to occur of the following events:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The tenth anniversary of the Grant Date so long as the Grantee remains employed with the Company or a Successor
	through such date;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The third anniversary of the date of the Grantee&#146;s termination of employment with the
	Company or a Successor, if the Grantee&#146;s employment terminates by reason of death or Permanent Disability;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(c)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Immediately upon the date of the Grantee&#146;s termination of employment by the Company or a Successor for Cause;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(d)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;One hundred and eighty (180)&nbsp;days after the date of the Grantee&#146;s termination of employment by the
	Company or a Successor without Cause (for any reason other than as set forth in Section 3.2(b));
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(e)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;One hundred
	and eighty (180)&nbsp;days after the date of the Grantee&#146;s termination of employment with the Company or a Successor by the Grantee for Good Reason;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	5
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage146"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(f)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The third anniversary of the date of the Grantee&#146;s termination of
	employment with the Company or a Successor by the Grantee upon Retirement; or
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(g)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Sixty (60)&nbsp;days after the
	date of the Grantee&#146;s termination of employment with the Company or a Successor by the Grantee without Good Reason (except due to Retirement, death or Permanent Disability).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	For the avoidance of doubt, for purposes of this Agreement, Grantee&#146;s employment shall not be deemed to have terminated so long as Grantee remains
	employed by any Service Recipient.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	ARTICLE IV
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<U>
	EXERCISE
</U>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;4.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Person
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Eligible
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	to
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Exercise
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	The Grantee may exercise only that portion of this Award that has both vested and become exercisable at the time Grantee desires to exercise
	this Award and that has not expired pursuant to Section&nbsp;3.2. During the lifetime of the Grantee, only the Grantee (or his or her duly authorized legal representative) may exercise the SARs granted pursuant to this Award or any portion thereof.
	After the death of the Grantee, any vested and exercisable portion of this Award may, prior to the time when such portion becomes unexercisable under Section&nbsp;3.2, be exercised by his personal representative or by any person empowered to do so
	under the Grantee&#146;s will or under the then applicable laws of descent and distribution.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;4.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Partial
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Exercise
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Any vested and exercisable portion of this Award, or the entire Award, if then wholly vested and exercisable, may be exercised in whole or in
	part at any time prior to the time when the Award or portion thereof becomes unexercisable under Section&nbsp;3.2.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	6
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage147"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;4.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Manner
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	of
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Exercise
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Subject to the Company&#146;s code of conduct and securities trading policies as in effect from time to time, this Award, or any exercisable
	portion thereof, may be exercised solely by delivering to the Company or its designated agent all of the following prior to the time when the Award or such portion becomes unexercisable under Section&nbsp;3.2:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Notice in writing (or such other medium acceptable to the Company or its designated agent) signed or acknowledged
	by the Grantee or other person then entitled to exercise the Award, stating the number of SARs subject to the Award in respect of which the Award is thereby being exercised, such notice complying with all applicable rules established by the
	Committee;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(i) Full payment (in cash or by check or by a combination thereof) to satisfy the minimum
	withholding tax obligation with respect to which the Award or portion thereof is exercised or (ii)&nbsp;indication that the Grantee elects to satisfy the withholding tax obligation through an arrangement that is compliant with the Sarbanes-Oxley Act
	of 2002 (and any other applicable laws and exchange rules) and that provides for the delivery of irrevocable instructions to a broker to sell Shares obtained upon the exercise of the Award and to deliver promptly to the Company an amount to satisfy
	the minimum withholding tax obligation that would otherwise be required to be paid by the Grantee to the Company pursuant to clause (i)&nbsp;of this subsection (b), or (iii)&nbsp;if made available by the Company, indication that the Grantee elects
	to have the number of Shares that would otherwise be issued to the Grantee upon exercise of such Award (or portion thereof) reduced by a number of Shares having an aggregate Fair Market Value, on the date of such exercise, equal to the payment to
	satisfy the minimum withholding tax obligation that would otherwise be required to be made by the Grantee to the Company pursuant to clause (i)&nbsp;of this subsection (b).
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(c)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If required by the Company, a bona fide written representation and agreement, in a form satisfactory to the
	Company, signed by the Grantee or other person then entitled to exercise such Award or portion thereof, stating that the shares of Common Stock are being acquired for his own account, for investment and without any present intention of distributing
	or reselling said shares or any of them except as may be permitted under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended (the &#147;
<U>
	Act
</U>
	&#148;), and then applicable rules and regulations thereunder, and that the Grantee or other person then entitled to
	exercise such Award or portion thereof will indemnify the Company against and hold it free and harmless from any loss, damage, expense or liability resulting to the Company if any sale or distribution of the shares by such person is contrary to the
	representation and agreement referred to above; provided, however, that the Company may, in its reasonable discretion, take whatever additional actions it deems reasonably necessary to ensure the observance and performance of such representation and
	agreement and to effect compliance with the Act and any other federal or state securities laws or regulations; and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(d)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event the Award or portion thereof shall be exercised pursuant to Section&nbsp;4.1 by any person or persons
	other than the Grantee, appropriate proof of the right of such person or persons to exercise the Award.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Without limiting the generality of the foregoing,
	the Company may require an opinion of counsel acceptable to it to the effect that any subsequent transfer of shares acquired on exercise of this Award (or portion thereof) does not violate
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	7
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage148"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	the Act, and may issue stop-transfer orders covering such Shares. Share certificates evidencing stock issued on exercise of any portion of this Award shall bear an appropriate legend referring to
	the provisions of subsection (c)&nbsp;above and the agreements herein. The written representation and agreement referred to in subsection (c)&nbsp;above shall, however, not be required if the shares to be issued pursuant to such exercise have been
	registered under the Act, and such registration is then effective in respect of such shares.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;4.4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Conditions
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	to
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Issuance
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	of
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Stock
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Certificates
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	The Shares issuable (whether by certificate or otherwise) upon the exercise of this Award, or any portion
	thereof, may be either previously authorized but unissued Shares or issued Shares, which have then been reacquired by the Company. Such Shares shall be fully paid and nonassessable. If share certificates are to be issued, the Company shall not be
	required to issue or deliver any certificate or certificates for Shares purchased upon the exercise of this Award or portion thereof prior to fulfillment of all of the following conditions:
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(a)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The obtaining of approval or other clearance from any state or federal governmental agency which the Committee
	shall, in its reasonable and good faith discretion, determine to be necessary or advisable; and
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	(b)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The lapse of
	such reasonable period of time following the exercise of the Award as the Committee may from time to time establish for reasons of administrative convenience or as may otherwise be required by applicable law.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;4.5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Rights
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	as
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Stockholder
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Except as otherwise provided in Section&nbsp;2.4 of this Agreement, the holder of any SARs subject to this Award shall not be, nor have any of
	the rights or privileges of, a stockholder of the Company in respect of any Shares issuable upon the exercise of this Award or any portion thereof unless and until certificates representing such Shares shall have been issued by the Company to such
	holder, or the Company or its designated agent has otherwise recorded the appropriate book entries evidencing Grantee&#146;s ownership of the Shares.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:24PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	ARTICLE V
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
<U>
	MISCELLANEOUS
</U>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:12PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;5.1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Administration
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	The Committee shall have the power to interpret the Plan and this Agreement and to adopt such rules for the administration, interpretation and
	application of the Plan as are consistent therewith and to interpret or revoke any
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT;MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT ; FONT-SIZE:8PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN" ALIGN="CENTER">
	8
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage149"></A>
<P STYLE='PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE:ALWAYS'>
<HR SIZE="3" STYLE="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:0PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	such rules. All actions taken and all interpretations and determinations made by the Committee shall be final and binding upon the Grantee, the Company and all other interested persons. No member
	of the Committee shall be personally liable for any action, determination or interpretation made in good faith with respect to the Plan or this Award. In its absolute discretion, the Board may at any time and from time to time exercise any and all
	rights and duties of the Committee under the Plan and this Agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;5.2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Award
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Not
</U>
<U>
</U>
<U>
	Transferable
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	No part of, or interest in, this Award shall be liable for the debts, contracts or engagements of the Grantee
	or his successors in interest or shall be subject to disposition by transfer, alienation, anticipation, pledge, encumbrance, assignment or any other means whether such disposition be voluntary or involuntary or by operation of law by judgment, levy,
	attachment, garnishment or any other legal or equitable proceedings (including bankruptcy), and any attempted disposition thereof shall be null and void and of no effect; provided, however, that this Section&nbsp;5.2 shall not prevent transfers by
	will or by the applicable laws of descent and distribution.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;5.3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Notices
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	Any notice to be given under the terms of this Agreement to the Company shall be addressed to the Company in care of its Secretary or its
	designee, and any notice to be given to the Grantee shall be addressed to him at the address (including an electronic address) reflected in the Company&#146;s books and records. By a notice given pursuant to this Section&nbsp;5.3, either party may
	hereafter designate a different address for notices to be given to him. Any notice, which is required to be given to the Grantee, shall, if the Grantee is then deceased, be given to the Grantee&#146;s personal representative if such representative
	has previously informed the Company of his status and address by written notice under this Section&nbsp;5.3. Any notice shall have been deemed duly given when (i)&nbsp;delivered in person, (ii)&nbsp;delivered in an electronic form approved by the
	Company, (iii)&nbsp;enclosed in a properly sealed envelope or wrapper addressed as aforesaid, deposited (with postage prepaid) in a post office or branch post office regularly maintained by the United States Postal Service, or (iv)&nbsp;enclosed in
	a properly sealed envelope or wrapper addressed as aforesaid, deposited (with fees prepaid) in an office regularly maintained by FedEx, UPS, or comparable
<FONT STYLE="WHITE-SPACE:NOWRAP">
	non-public
</FONT>
	mail carrier.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">

	Titles are provided herein for convenience only and are not to serve as a basis for interpretation or construction of this Agreement. The
	masculine pronoun shall include the feminine and neuter, and the singular the plural, where the context so indicates.

	terms of this Agreement are governed by the terms of the Plan, and in the case of any inconsistency between the terms of this Agreement and the terms of the Plan, the terms of the Plan shall govern.

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">

	states that it is amending this Agreement.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">

</U>

<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	The laws of the State of Delaware shall govern the interpretation, validity and performance of the terms of this Agreement regardless of the
	law that might be applied under principles of conflicts of laws.
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:18PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
<B>
	Section&nbsp;5.8&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<U>
	Arbitration
</U>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-TOP:6PT; MARGIN-BOTTOM:0PT; TEXT-INDENT:8%; FONT-SIZE:10PT; FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN">
	In the event of any controversy among the parties hereto arising out of, or relating to, this Agreement which cannot be settled amicably by the
	parties, such controversy shall be finally, exclusively and conclusively settled by mandatory arbitration conducted expeditiously in accordance with the American Arbitration Association rules, by a single independent arbitrator. Such arbitration
	process shall take place within the Nashville, Tennessee metropolitan area. The decision of the arbitrator shall be final and binding upon all parties hereto and shall be rendered pursuant to a written decision, which contains a detailed recital of
	the arbitrator&#146;s reasoning. Judgment upon the award rendered may be entered in any court having jurisdiction thereof. Each party shall bear its own legal fees and expenses, unless otherwise determined by the arbitrator. If the Grantee
	substantially prevails on any of his or her substantive legal claims, then the Company shall reimburse all legal fees and arbitration fees incurred by the Grantee to arbitrate the dispute.
</P>
